<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" ?>

<Patch>
	<Operation Class="PatchOperationConditional">
	<!-- Does this exist? -->
		<xpath>/Defs/ThingDef[defName="AM_BlocksPristineLimestone"]</xpath>
		<!-- If it does, add this. -->
		<match Class="PatchOperationAdd">
			<success>Always</success>
			<xpath>/Defs</xpath>
			<value>
				<terrainDef ParentName="FloorBase" Name="TSP_AM_PristineMarbleBase" Abstract="True">
					<renderPrecedence Inherit="False">240</renderPrecedence>
					<description>Of all the marble in the world, no marble is so perfectly carved or handled as the fabled Pristine Marble. Hailing from Old Earth's Ancient Egypt, quarries of the stone have since been located on the Rim, but they are extremely rare. To make a mosaic tile of these is to exhibit luxury that reciprocates that of a Glitter World. \n Taking a very long time to lay, the mosaic is the most attractive flooring that can be found in a Roman home. It can also be found in any mansion of other civilized peoples.</description>
					<designatorDropdown>TSP_AR_SpecialMarble_Mosaik</designatorDropdown>
					<color Inherit="False">(170,157,125)</color>
					<statBases>
						<MarketValue Inherit="False">12</MarketValue> <!-- To prevent it from giving insane amounts of Wealth based on the Work to Build -->
						<Beauty Inherit="False">8</Beauty>
						<Cleanliness Inherit="False">0.5</Cleanliness>
						<WorkToBuild Inherit="False">5600</WorkToBuild>
					</statBases>
					<researchPrerequisites>
						<li>Stonecutting</li>
						<li MayRequire="oskarpotocki.vfe.classical">VFEC_Mosaics</li>
					</researchPrerequisites>
					<costList Inherit="False">
						<AM_BlocksPristineLimestone Inherit="False">10</AM_BlocksPristineLimestone>
					</costList>
					<constructionSkillPrerequisite>8</constructionSkillPrerequisite>
					<tags>
						<li>Floor</li>
						<li>FineFloor</li>
					</tags>
				</terrainDef>
			</value>
		</match>
		<!-- If the first XPATH does not exist, the original code stands. -->
	</Operation>
	
